  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Peel and grate the<strong> apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, discarding the core<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them&nbsp;finely</p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>Italian hard cheese&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated apple</strong>, <strong>chopped thyme leaves</strong>, <strong>grated cheese</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and<strong> beef mince</strong> to a large bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix&nbsp;very thoroughly until fully combined</p>\r\n<p>Divide the mixture into 12 <span class=\"text-danger\">[24]</span> and shape them into meatballs</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong>over a medium-low heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the&nbsp;<strong>meatballs</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 3-4 min or until browned on all sides</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop the<strong>&nbsp;brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and&nbsp;finely chop (or grate) the&nbsp;<strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer the&nbsp;<strong>meatballs&nbsp;</strong>to a plate and set aside until later&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Return the pan to a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the&nbsp;<strong>chopped onion</strong>&nbsp;with a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 5 min or until softened</p>\r\n<p>Once softened, add the&nbsp;<strong>chopped garlic&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 1 min further&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1046.-step-4-x200.jpg",
